Doc,<br><br>
If you will look back at our initial postings way back when, you will find the dialogue much different than what has taken place recently.<br><br>
I like to think that the purpose of sites such as this is to enable people to tear down the fences that separate them. People who happen to come here, and follow from the beginning can see not only a change in dialogue, they can also see a real effort to come to a reconciliation.<br>
 <br>
My opinion is that the Vietnam Memorial was not built for me. It was constructed to honor those who never made it back. <br><br>
The only way that we can learn and accomplish the achieving of ideals is if we make a place at the table for everyone. It is necessary to look inside our own hearts.<br><br>
There is a poem on my website which was written by someone you may identify with. A person who unexpectedly reaches a realization while visiting Arlington National Cemetary. It is difficult to read when I get to the end and it says:<br><br>
&quot;No, in this cynical time<br>
It is said that no one believes in anything<br>
Tens of thousands of stones say otherwise&quot;<br><br>

